# Project Context: Product Design Leads

This is a Next.js 16 + TypeScript + Supabase monorepo for a solo product designer. It is organized in 4 phases, all sharing the same stack, design system, and Vercel deploy pipeline.

## Stack

- Next.js 16 App Router + TypeScript
- Tailwind v4 + shadcn/ui
- Supabase (Auth, Postgres, Storage, RLS)
- Gemini Flash Lite (AI features)
- Vercel (hosting + preview deploys)
- Linear (project management, team key: PRO)

## Phase 0 — Foundations (Urgent, in progress)

Shared base for all phases.

- Repo init, Supabase clients, design tokens, ESLint/Prettier/Husky/CI, Vercel deploy.
- Linear issues: PRO-5 through PRO-10 (identifiers use prefix F0-*).
- Gate to Phase 1: all F0 issues done, CI green, domain live.

## Phase 1 — Portfolio Web (High priority, backlog)

Public portfolio at `avinro.com` with 3 case studies, SEO, and a contact form.

- Key pages: `/`, `/work`, `/work/[slug]`, `/about`, `/contact`, `/lab`.
- KPIs: Lighthouse mobile >= 90, LCP < 2s, CLS < 0.1.
- Linear issues: PRO identifiers with prefix F1-*.

## Phase 2 — Outreach LimaLeads (Medium priority, backlog)

Private backoffice for Apollo lead import, pipeline management, email sequences, and AI email drafting with Gemini Flash Lite.

- Data: `companies`, `contacts`, `leads`, `sequences`, `sequence_runs`, `messages`, `templates`.
- KPIs: Apollo CSV import < 60s for 1k leads, pipeline >= 5 stages, Gemini draft < 3s.
- Linear issues: PRO identifiers with prefix F2-*.
- Gate to Phase 3: Phase 1 live, Phase 2 KPIs met.

## Phase 3 — Client Portal (Low priority, backlog)

Private per-client space with project status, deliverables, feedback, and AI summaries.

- Auth: Supabase magic link. RLS by `account_id`. Owner sees everything; clients see only their account.
- Data: `accounts`, `account_members`, `projects`, `milestones`, `deliverables`, `comments`, `intake_forms`.
- Linear issues: PRO identifiers with prefix F3-*.

## Decision rules

- When requirements conflict, defer to the Linear issue's Acceptance Criteria.
- Work phases sequentially: do not start Phase N+1 issues until the gate for Phase N is met.
- Never commit secrets (`.env`, credentials).
- Comments in code must be in English.
- All UI must be built mobile-first.
